The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
		 Monday, June 14, 2004  Q amp;A				 Index of inflation
																																																																																													Is investment in CANPEP 1992 equity-linked scheme under Section 88CCB eligible for cost inflation index benefit for calculation of long-term capital loss or gain on redemption after 10 years? 																																																																													R. K. Singhal, Durgapur
																																																																																													Mutual fund units held for more than 12 months are considered as capital assets. Since transfer of such asset gives rise to long-term capital gain or loss, it is eligible for cost inflation index benefit.																																					Senior status																																																																																															At which age can a person claim senior citizen status and what is the income tax rebate and deduction available to senior citizens? 																																																																													Gangacharan Dutta, Calcutta
																																																																																													A person can claim senior citizen status at the age of 65 years. A senior citizen can claim deduction for payment of medical insurance premium up to Rs 15,000 and for medical treatment up to Rs 60,000. They can further claim a tax rebate of up to Rs 20,000.																																					My better half																																																																																															My wife is a senior citizen and has income from post office monthly income scheme, RBI taxable bond and Varishtha Pension Bima Yojana. Can she also get income tax rebate separately as a senior citizen?																																																																													K. V. Sethy, Calcutta
																																																																																													Yes, she can get income tax rebate separately as senior citizen on filing returns.																																					Cover for your home																																																																																															I wish to take a home loan of Rs 7.5 lakh from State Bank of India and I am interested in using home loan insurance facility. What are the precautions to be taken while taking home loan with insurance scheme since I do not want my wife to face problems in the event of my death?																																																																													R. K. Kapoor, Calcutta
																																																																																													Home loan insurance policy is termed as mortgage redemption policies and are offered by many insurance companies. It is prudent to take such a policy. In the event of your death, the insurance company will repay your debt and your wife wont have to face any problems.												If you have any queries about investing or taxes or a high-cost purchase you are planning, mail to: btgraphabpmail.com, or write to: Business Telegraph, 6 Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta 700 001.
